channel.title: [317] Teleports on the emote tab [317]
channel.description:
Ok guys, i am trying to make a new server and the base i downloaded has home in the emotes tab..how do i change the coords in which it teleports you to? i've tried the case (168) and it isnt there..ive also typed in the current x coord of where it teleports me to. And i have found nothing, so could someone tell me where i can find it?
Thanks.

item.title: [317] Teleports on the emote tab [317]
item.dc:creator: @chassy13 Chassy13
item.description:
@chassy13 wrote:

case 168: if (teleblock == true) { sendMessage("A magical force stops you from teleporting."); } else { customCommand("home"); } break;

Since that packet is calling the ‘home’ customCommand,

if (command.equalsIgnoreCase("home")) { teleportToX = 3248; teleportToY = 9364; sendMessage("You teleport to Home.");

You can easily just add your own coordinates though and make it not call any command at all.
